b'     Dear Students,     Topic:  Know more about applying for higher studies in ETH Zurich, Federal Institute of Technology in Switzerland  Date:  Time:  Venue :  Hall 3, IC & SR   Description:  Be a part of a session on ETH Zurich, one of the leading international universities for technology, by two representatives from the institute. This talk will cover the following key information for engineering students to apply to ETH Zurich for higher studies.  Universities and courses available for bachelor, masters and doctorate programs Eligibility to study in Switzerland  Application process </li Scholarship opportunities     After the session, there will be a Q&A round and interaction to answer any further questions.     About ETH Zurich:     ETH Zurich, Federal Institute of Technology has ranked 8 th  by QS Ranking 2016 and ranked 9 th  by Times Ranking 2015. It has:  43 Master courses in technology like Mechanical Engineering , Robotics Systems and control, Biomedical Strong links with research and practice 22 spinoffs, 82 new patents, 298 cooperation agreements Encourages entrepreneurial approach  Speakers Bio    Raghav Khanna   Doctoral student  / Autonomous Systems Lab, ETH Zurich  Raghav Khanna did his Bachelors in Mechanical Engineering from IIT Kanpur and his Masters at ETH Zurich where he was awarded the ETH Medal for building a novel thermal energy storage for solar power during his master thesis. He is currently a graduate student at the Autonomous Systems Lab     Stefan Bertschi   Engineer  / Autonomous Systems Lab, ETH Zurich  Stefan Bertschi is working as an engineer at the Autonomous Systems Lab of ETH Zurich since 9 years, where he leads the robotics laboratory, supports the research teams and established a schooloutreachprogram.   With regards Kavitha                   K avitha G.R (Ms )  Manager    International Relations Office of International Relations l   2 nd Floor, IC & SR Building   I ndian Institute of Technology Madras  l  Chennai    600 036